This paper proposes a learning rule for synaptic plasticity in spiking neural networks, which is a topic related to neural networks and machine learning. The focus is on neuromorphic hardware implementation, which suggests a connection to embedded systems and hardware architecture. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Other possible categories include cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.ET (Embedded Systems).
